The paper deals with the concept of dimension in the context of computational complexity, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of gales, which are a generalization of martingales, suggests a connection to probability theory and information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also discusses internal dimension theories in various complexity classes, which could place it in cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) or cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
